{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":543,"text":"On March 10, 2011,"},{"time":3286,"text":"I was in Cambridge at the MIT Media Lab"},{"time":6293,"text":"meeting with faculty, students and staff,"},{"time":9522,"text":"and we were trying to figure out whether"},{"time":11311,"text":"I should be the next director."}]},{"cues":[{"time":13671,"text":"That night, at midnight,"},{"time":16040,"text":"a magnitude 9 earthquake"},{"time":17810,"text":"hit off of the Pacific coast of Japan."},{"time":20676,"text":"My wife and family were in Japan,"},{"time":22961,"text":"and as the news started to come in,"},{"time":26271,"text":"I was panicking."},{"time":27970,"text":"I was looking at the news streams"},{"time":29232,"text":"and listening to the press conferences"},{"time":32060,"text":"of the government officials"},{"time":34270,"text":"and the Tokyo Power Company,"},{"time":35860,"text":"and hearing about this explosion"},{"time":38411,"text":"at the nuclear reactors"},{"time":39610,"text":"and this cloud of fallout"},{"time":41291,"text":"that was headed towards our house"},{"time":43190,"text":"which was only about 200 kilometers away."},{"time":46089,"text":"And the people on TV weren't telling us"},{"time":48920,"text":"anything that we wanted to hear."},{"time":50860,"text":"I wanted to know what was going on with the reactor,"},{"time":52820,"text":"what was going on with the radiation,"},{"time":54242,"text":"whether my family was in danger."}]},{"cues":[{"time":56570,"text":"So I did what instinctively felt like the right thing,"},{"time":59759,"text":"which was to go onto the Internet"},{"time":61430,"text":"and try to figure out"},{"time":62772,"text":"if I could take matters into my own hands."},{"time":65183,"text":"On the Net, I found there were a lot of other people"},{"time":67024,"text":"like me trying to figure out what was going on,"},{"time":69090,"text":"and together we sort of loosely formed a group"},{"time":71306,"text":"and we called it Safecast,"},{"time":73777,"text":"and we decided we were going to try"},{"time":74949,"text":"to measure the radiation"},{"time":76695,"text":"and get the data out to everybody else,"},{"time":78469,"text":"because it was clear that the government"},{"time":80141,"text":"wasn't going to be doing this for us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":83043,"text":"Three years later,"},{"time":84460,"text":"we have 16 million data points,"},{"time":87554,"text":"we have designed our own Geiger counters"},{"time":90299,"text":"that you can download the designs"},{"time":91952,"text":"and plug it into the network."},{"time":92826,"text":"We have an app that shows you"},{"time":94730,"text":"most of the radiation in Japan\nand other parts of the world."},{"time":97757,"text":"We are arguably one of the most successful"},{"time":99962,"text":"citizen science projects in the world,"},{"time":101817,"text":"and we have created"},{"time":104169,"text":"the largest open dataset of radiation measurements."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107670,"text":"And the interesting thing here"},{"time":110412,"text":"is how did — (Applause) — Thank you."},{"time":115060,"text":"How did a bunch of amateurs"},{"time":117151,"text":"who really didn't know what we were doing"},{"time":119320,"text":"somehow come together"},{"time":121009,"text":"and do what NGOs and the government"},{"time":124193,"text":"were completely incapable of doing?"},{"time":126611,"text":"And I would suggest that this has something to do"},{"time":129369,"text":"with the Internet. It's not a fluke."},{"time":131129,"text":"It wasn't luck, and it wasn't because it was us."},{"time":133980,"text":"It helped that it was an event"},{"time":135398,"text":"that pulled everybody together,"},{"time":137033,"text":"but it was a new way of doing things"},{"time":138791,"text":"that was enabled by the Internet"},{"time":140870,"text":"and a lot of the other things that were going on,"},{"time":142462,"text":"and I want to talk a little bit about"},{"time":144475,"text":"what those new principles are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147144,"text":"So remember before the Internet? (Laughter)"},{"time":151952,"text":"I call this B.I. Okay?"},{"time":153740,"text":"So, in B.I., life was simple."},{"time":157351,"text":"Things were Euclidian, Newtonian,"},{"time":160097,"text":"somewhat predictable."},{"time":161556,"text":"People actually tried to predict the future,"},{"time":163966,"text":"even the economists."},{"time":165680,"text":"And then the Internet happened,"},{"time":168894,"text":"and the world became extremely complex,"},{"time":170965,"text":"extremely low-cost, extremely fast,"},{"time":173602,"text":"and those Newtonian laws"},{"time":175720,"text":"that we so dearly cherished"},{"time":177519,"text":"turned out to be just local ordinances,"},{"time":179716,"text":"and what we found was that in this"},{"time":181467,"text":"completely unpredictable world"},{"time":184080,"text":"that most of the people who were surviving"},{"time":186112,"text":"were working with sort of a different set of principles,"},{"time":189445,"text":"and I want to talk a little bit about that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192076,"text":"Before the Internet, if you remember,"},{"time":193440,"text":"when we tried to create services,"},{"time":195345,"text":"what you would do is you'd create"},{"time":196371,"text":"the hardware layer and the\nnetwork layer and the software"},{"time":198683,"text":"and it would cost millions of dollars"},{"time":200711,"text":"to do anything that was substantial."},{"time":203018,"text":"So when it costs millions of dollars\nto do something substantial,"},{"time":205457,"text":"what you would do is you'd get an MBA"},{"time":207529,"text":"who would write a plan"},{"time":208987,"text":"and get the money"},{"time":209930,"text":"from V.C.s or big companies,"},{"time":211674,"text":"and then you'd hire the designers and the engineers,"},{"time":213787,"text":"and they'd build the thing."},{"time":214810,"text":"This is the Before Internet, B.I., innovation model."},{"time":219429,"text":"What happened after the Internet was"},{"time":221736,"text":"the cost of innovation went down so much"},{"time":223492,"text":"because the cost of collaboration,\nthe cost of distribution,"},{"time":225979,"text":"the cost of communication, and Moore's Law"},{"time":228622,"text":"made it so that the cost of trying a new thing"},{"time":231298,"text":"became nearly zero,"},{"time":232692,"text":"and so you would have Google, Facebook, Yahoo,"},{"time":234961,"text":"students that didn't have permission —"},{"time":236732,"text":"permissionless innovation —"},{"time":238105,"text":"didn't have permission, didn't have PowerPoints,"},{"time":239725,"text":"they just built the thing,"},{"time":241828,"text":"then they raised the money,"},{"time":243272,"text":"and then they sort of figured out a business plan"},{"time":245473,"text":"and maybe later on they hired some MBAs."},{"time":247830,"text":"So the Internet caused innovation,"},{"time":250141,"text":"at least in software and services,"},{"time":251265,"text":"to go from an MBA-driven innovation model"},{"time":254124,"text":"to a designer-engineer-driven innovation model,"},{"time":258027,"text":"and it pushed innovation to the edges,"},{"time":260125,"text":"to the dorm rooms, to the startups,"},{"time":261671,"text":"away from the large institutions,"},{"time":263357,"text":"the stodgy old institutions that had the power"},{"time":265712,"text":"and the money and the authority."},{"time":267399,"text":"And we all know this. We all know\nthis happened on the Internet."},{"time":270008,"text":"It turns out it's happening in other things, too."},{"time":272773,"text":"Let me give you some examples."}]},{"cues":[{"time":276015,"text":"So at the Media Lab, we don't just do hardware."},{"time":278800,"text":"We do all kinds of things."},{"time":279842,"text":"We do biology, we do hardware,"},{"time":281727,"text":"and Nicholas Negroponte\nfamously said, \"Demo or die,\""},{"time":285348,"text":"as opposed to \"Publish or perish,\""},{"time":287070,"text":"which was the traditional academic way of thinking."},{"time":289313,"text":"And he often said, the demo only has to work once,"},{"time":292875,"text":"because the primary mode of us impacting the world"},{"time":295691,"text":"was through large companies"},{"time":297469,"text":"being inspired by us"},{"time":298732,"text":"and creating products like\nthe Kindle or Lego Mindstorms."},{"time":302248,"text":"But today, with the ability"},{"time":304190,"text":"to deploy things into the real world at such low cost,"},{"time":306499,"text":"I'm changing the motto now,"},{"time":308649,"text":"and this is the official public statement."},{"time":310462,"text":"I'm officially saying, \"Deploy or die.\""},{"time":312959,"text":"You have to get the stuff into the real world"},{"time":315180,"text":"for it to really count,"},{"time":316536,"text":"and sometimes it will be large companies,"},{"time":318415,"text":"and Nicholas can talk about satellites."},{"time":320372,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":321658,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":322740,"text":"But we should be getting out there ourselves"},{"time":324514,"text":"and not depending on large\ninstitutions to do it for us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":328098,"text":"So last year, we sent a bunch\nof students to Shenzhen,"},{"time":330800,"text":"and they sat on the factory floors"},{"time":332380,"text":"with the innovators in Shenzhen, and it was amazing."},{"time":334685,"text":"What was happening there"},{"time":336162,"text":"was you would have these manufacturing devices,"},{"time":338346,"text":"and they weren't making prototypes or PowerPoints."},{"time":340539,"text":"They were fiddling with the manufacturing equipment"},{"time":343004,"text":"and innovating right on the\nmanufacturing equipment."},{"time":346214,"text":"The factory was in the designer,"},{"time":348100,"text":"and the designer was literally in the factory."},{"time":350374,"text":"And so what you would do is,"},{"time":352000,"text":"you'd go down to the stalls"},{"time":353241,"text":"and you would see these cell phones."},{"time":355797,"text":"So instead of starting little websites"},{"time":358322,"text":"like the kids in Palo Alto do,"},{"time":359870,"text":"the kids in Shenzhen make new cell phones."},{"time":362410,"text":"They make new cell phones like kids in Palo Alto"},{"time":365107,"text":"make websites,"},{"time":366365,"text":"and so there's a rainforest"},{"time":368478,"text":"of innovation going on in the cell phone."},{"time":370034,"text":"What they do is, they make a cell phone,"},{"time":371634,"text":"go down to the stall, they sell some,"},{"time":373858,"text":"they look at the other kids' stuff, go up,"},{"time":376183,"text":"make a couple thousand more, go down."},{"time":378774,"text":"Doesn't this sound like a software thing?"},{"time":380765,"text":"It sounds like agile software development,"},{"time":382412,"text":"A/B testing and iteration,"},{"time":385340,"text":"and what we thought you could only do with software"},{"time":387423,"text":"kids in Shenzhen are doing this in hardware."},{"time":389693,"text":"My next fellow, I hope, is going to be"},{"time":391160,"text":"one of these innovators from Shenzhen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":392645,"text":"And so what you see is"},{"time":394310,"text":"that is pushing innovation to the edges."},{"time":396279,"text":"We talk about 3D printers and stuff like that,"},{"time":398384,"text":"and that's great, but this is Limor."},{"time":400375,"text":"She is one of our favorite graduates,"},{"time":402634,"text":"and she is standing in front of a Samsung"},{"time":404710,"text":"Techwin Pick and Place Machine."},{"time":406543,"text":"This thing can put 23,000 components per hour"},{"time":410467,"text":"onto an electronics board."},{"time":412460,"text":"This is a factory in a box."},{"time":414283,"text":"So what used to take a factory full of workers"},{"time":416781,"text":"working by hand"},{"time":417800,"text":"in this little box in New York,"},{"time":419509,"text":"she's able to have effectively —"},{"time":420559,"text":"She doesn't actually have to go to Shenzhen"},{"time":422192,"text":"to do this manufacturing."},{"time":423436,"text":"She can buy this box and she can manufacture it."},{"time":425697,"text":"So manufacturing, the cost of innovation,"},{"time":427940,"text":"the cost of prototyping, distribution,\nmanufacturing, hardware,"},{"time":430630,"text":"is getting so low"},{"time":432093,"text":"that innovation is being pushed to the edges"},{"time":434410,"text":"and students and startups are being able to build it."},{"time":436838,"text":"This is a recent thing, but this will happen"},{"time":438716,"text":"and this will change"},{"time":440199,"text":"just like it did with software."}]},{"cues":[{"time":442624,"text":"Sorona is a DuPont process"},{"time":445870,"text":"that uses a genetically engineered microbe"},{"time":448890,"text":"to turn corn sugar into polyester."},{"time":452840,"text":"It's 30 percent more efficient\nthan the fossil fuel method,"},{"time":455318,"text":"and it's much better for the environment."},{"time":458977,"text":"Genetic engineering and bioengineering"},{"time":460382,"text":"are creating a whole bunch"},{"time":461913,"text":"of great new opportunities"},{"time":463671,"text":"for chemistry, for computation, for memory."},{"time":466500,"text":"We will probably be doing a lot,\nobviously doing health things,"},{"time":468550,"text":"but we will probably be growing chairs"},{"time":470754,"text":"and buildings soon."},{"time":471794,"text":"The problem is, Sorona costs\nabout 400 million dollars"},{"time":475704,"text":"and took seven years to build."},{"time":477085,"text":"It kind of reminds you of the old mainframe days."},{"time":480164,"text":"The thing is, the cost of innovation"},{"time":482656,"text":"in bioengineering is also going down."},{"time":484242,"text":"This is desktop gene sequencer."},{"time":486211,"text":"It used to cost millions and millions\nof dollars to sequence genes."},{"time":489765,"text":"Now you can do it on a desktop like this,"},{"time":491509,"text":"and kids can do this in dorm rooms."},{"time":493602,"text":"This is Gen9 gene assembler,"},{"time":496290,"text":"and so right now when you try to print a gene,"},{"time":498369,"text":"what you do is somebody in a factory"},{"time":499637,"text":"with pipettes puts the thing together by hand,"},{"time":501577,"text":"you have one error per 100 base pairs,"},{"time":503928,"text":"and it takes a long time and costs a lot of money."},{"time":506504,"text":"This new device"},{"time":507890,"text":"assembles genes on a chip,"},{"time":509564,"text":"and instead of one error per 100 base pairs,"},{"time":511713,"text":"it's one error per 10,000 base pairs."},{"time":513839,"text":"In this lab, we will have the world's capacity"},{"time":516584,"text":"of gene printing within a year,"},{"time":518687,"text":"200 million base pairs a year."},{"time":521299,"text":"This is kind of like when we went"},{"time":523862,"text":"from transistor radios wrapped by hand"},{"time":526123,"text":"to the Pentium."},{"time":527394,"text":"This is going to become the\nPentium of bioengineering,"},{"time":529790,"text":"pushing bioengineering into the hands"},{"time":531826,"text":"of dorm rooms and startup companies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":534427,"text":"So it's happening in software and in hardware"},{"time":537200,"text":"and bioengineering,"},{"time":538163,"text":"and so this is a fundamental new\nway of thinking about innovation."},{"time":541444,"text":"It's a bottom-up innovation, it's democratic,"},{"time":544121,"text":"it's chaotic, it's hard to control."},{"time":546325,"text":"It's not bad, but it's very different,"},{"time":548632,"text":"and I think that the traditional rules that we have"},{"time":550599,"text":"for institutions don't work anymore,"},{"time":552671,"text":"and most of us here"},{"time":554350,"text":"operate with a different set of principles."},{"time":557433,"text":"One of my favorite principles is the power of pull,"},{"time":560269,"text":"which is the idea of pulling resources"},{"time":562560,"text":"from the network as you need them"},{"time":564326,"text":"rather than stocking them in the center"},{"time":566171,"text":"and controlling everything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":567756,"text":"So in the case of the Safecast story,"},{"time":570520,"text":"I didn't know anything when\nthe earthquake happened,"},{"time":572362,"text":"but I was able to find Sean"},{"time":573990,"text":"who was the hackerspace community organizer,"},{"time":576186,"text":"and Peter, the analog hardware hacker"},{"time":577972,"text":"who made our first Geiger counter,"},{"time":579688,"text":"and Dan, who built the Three Mile Island"},{"time":581686,"text":"monitoring system after the\nThree Mile Island meltdown."},{"time":585020,"text":"And these people I wouldn't have been able to find"},{"time":587406,"text":"beforehand and probably were better"},{"time":589840,"text":"that I found them just in time from the network."}]},{"cues":[{"time":592967,"text":"I'm a three-time college dropout,"},{"time":594834,"text":"so learning over education"},{"time":596507,"text":"is very near and dear to my heart,"},{"time":597932,"text":"but to me, education is what people do to you"},{"time":600456,"text":"and learning is what you do to yourself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":603455,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":607231,"text":"And it feels like, and I'm biased,"},{"time":608990,"text":"it feels like they're trying to make you memorize"},{"time":611787,"text":"the whole encyclopedia before\nthey let you go out and play,"},{"time":614901,"text":"and to me, I've got Wikipedia on my cell phone,"},{"time":618998,"text":"and it feels like they assume"},{"time":620701,"text":"you're going to be on top of some mountain"},{"time":622488,"text":"all by yourself with a number 2 pencil"},{"time":624949,"text":"trying to figure out what to do"},{"time":626332,"text":"when in fact you're always going to be connected,"},{"time":628448,"text":"you're always going to have friends,"},{"time":630093,"text":"and you can pull Wikipedia\nup whenever you need it,"},{"time":632052,"text":"and what you need to learn is how to learn."},{"time":635500,"text":"In the case of Safecast, a bunch of amateurs"},{"time":638144,"text":"when we started three years ago,"},{"time":639742,"text":"I would argue that we probably as a group"},{"time":642250,"text":"know more than any other organization"},{"time":644666,"text":"about how to collect data and publish data"},{"time":647875,"text":"and do citizen science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":650647,"text":"Compass over maps."},{"time":651767,"text":"So this one, the idea is that the cost of writing a plan"},{"time":655492,"text":"or mapping something is getting so expensive"},{"time":658595,"text":"and it's not very accurate or useful."},{"time":661768,"text":"So in the Safecast story, we\nknew we needed to collect data,"},{"time":664880,"text":"we knew we wanted to publish the data,"},{"time":667303,"text":"and instead of trying to come up with the exact plan,"},{"time":670192,"text":"we first said, oh, let's get Geiger counters."},{"time":672600,"text":"Oh, they've run out."},{"time":674366,"text":"Let's build them. There aren't enough sensors."},{"time":676369,"text":"Okay, then we can make a mobile Geiger counter."},{"time":678596,"text":"We can drive around. We can get volunteers."},{"time":680643,"text":"We don't have enough money. Let's Kickstarter it."},{"time":682522,"text":"We could not have planned this whole thing,"},{"time":684513,"text":"but by having a very strong compass,"},{"time":686257,"text":"we eventually got to where we were going,"},{"time":687692,"text":"and to me it's very similar to\nagile software development,"},{"time":690110,"text":"but this idea of compasses is very important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":693468,"text":"So I think the good news is"},{"time":695409,"text":"that even though the world is extremely complex,"},{"time":698920,"text":"what you need to do is very simple."},{"time":701302,"text":"I think it's about stopping this notion"},{"time":704000,"text":"that you need to plan everything,"},{"time":705572,"text":"you need to stock everything,"},{"time":706664,"text":"and you need to be so prepared,"},{"time":708134,"text":"and focus on being connected,"},{"time":711128,"text":"always learning,"},{"time":712979,"text":"fully aware,"},{"time":714840,"text":"and super present."}]},{"cues":[{"time":716620,"text":"So I don't like the word \"futurist.\""},{"time":719566,"text":"I think we should be now-ists,"},{"time":725181,"text":"like we are right now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":727227,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":729070,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}